# HOWTO - Setup and Configuration

## Local Development

Develop on the CLI (localhost):

```bash
cd ~/dev/vim4rabbit
claude
```

## Setup Jira

1. Atlassian.com > Profile > Security > API Tokens > Create token
2. Install the official Atlassian MCP server with Claude CLI:

```bash
claude mcp add --transport sse atlassian https://mcp.atlassian.com/v1/sse -s user
```

3. In Claude CLI: `/mcp` > atlassian > authenticate/connect

## Setup pytest Framework

Allow direnv to load env vars for the Python test env (only need to run once; it will error the first time and mention running `direnv allow`):

```bash
cd ~/dev/vim4rabbit && direnv allow
```

Run tests:

```bash
python -m pytest tests/ -v
```

Run tests with coverage:

```bash
.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ --cov=vim4rabbit --cov-report=term-missing
```
